WEBVTT

00:04:29.920 --> 00:04:32.016
Now, when you view trust
through this lens,

00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:35.696
it starts to explain
why it has the unique capacity

00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:38.816
to enable us to cope with uncertainty,

00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:41.856
to place our faith in strangers,

00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:43.760
to keep moving forward.

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:47.176
Human beings are remarkable

00:04:47.200 --> 00:04:48.880
at taking trust leaps.

00:04:49.400 --> 00:04:52.376
Do you remember the first time
you put your credit card details

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:53.616
into a website?

00:04:53.640 --> 00:04:54.976
That's a trust leap.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.936
I distinctly remember telling my dad

00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:03.216
that I wanted to buy a navy blue
secondhand Peugeot on eBay,